<TEXT>
<P>
 Jules and Jim (Bravo Thursday at 6 and 11 p.m.) is Francois Truffaut's 
groundbreaking 1961 romantic triangle, the French film that set the standard 
for a generation of American bohemian wanna-bes; a rare cable appearance. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lost World (AMC Saturday at 3 a.m.) is a remarkable 1925 silent with 
great, seminal stop-motion dinosaur battles. 
</P>
