<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: ENVIRONMENT: GROUP PLANS VALLEY-OCEAN TRAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Topanga-based group has announced an effort to establish the first 
continuous trail system between the San Fernando Valley and the Pacific Ocean. 
</P>
<P>
 Deborah Stern, president of the nonprofit Santa Maria Trails and Parks Assn., 
said the group's goal is to help develop a trail for hikers and horseback 
riders across the Santa Monica Mountains from the Valley to Topanga State 
Beach. 
</P>
</TEXT>
