<P>
 JON JANG & THE PAN-ASIAN ARKESTRA 
</P>
<P>
 "Tiananmen!" 
</P>
<P>
 Soul Note  
</P>
<P>
 * * * 1/2 
</P>
<P>
 Jang's first Soul Note album was disjointed but there's no trace of that 
problem on "Tiananmen!" The Bay Area pianist's ensemble -- augmented by guest 
James Newton (flute) -- evokes a myriad of moods by deftly blending jazz and 
Asian music elements and instrumentation, fiery improvisation, and provocative 
ensemble packages and arrangements.One brief portion halfway through "Fifth 
Modernization" tells the story of this constantly inventive, changing music -- 
an ensemble melody played by Asian instruments suddenly shifts gears to four 
hard-swinging, horn-dominated bars a la Mingus and then seamlessly slips back 
to the melody again. 
</P>
<P>
 New albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three 
stars (good) and four stars (excellent). DON SNOWDEN 
