<P>
 * * * Various artists, "In the Name of the Father" soundtrack, Island. An 
Irish all-star team contributes to this above-average soundtrack. Bono and 
Gavin Friday co-wrote and duet on two songs, both creepy, cannily crafted, 
percussive delights -- if hardly hits; Sinead O'Connor, in her prettily tense 
mode, sings a third insinuating big-beat ballad by the pair.Period rockers from 
Jimi Hendrix, Thin Lizzy and others make the cut, along with score excerpts by 
Trevor Jones. 
