<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE HOCHMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SYMBOL MAN RETURNS: What was all that again about Prince's retirement? 
</P>
<P>
 You may have heard that the Purple One, who declared last year that he is 
going to stop recording new music, has a new single, "The Most Beautiful Girl 
in the World," coming on Valentine's Day.But now we hear that he's also working 
in a Los Angeles recording studio on an album that could be in the stores by 
summer.  
</P>
<P>
 Karen Lee, vice president of media communications at Prince's Paisley Park 
company, would not confirm plans for an album, but said that a package of 
remixes of the single may be released.  
</P>
<P>
 In a twist, the single will not be distributed by Warner Bros. Records, the 
company that funds Paisley Park. Both Lee and a Warner Bros. spokesman said 
that it was agreed that the single could benefit from independent distribution 
in order to try to reach "new audiences." (The recording will be "previewed" 
during the Miss USA pageant telecast Feb. 11 on CBS.) 
</P>
<P>
 Lee said that Prince does have several new projects in the works, including 
new dance projects in the wake of the Joffrey Ballet's successful use of his 
music and the planned opening of more Prince clothing and accessories stores 
modeled on one opened last year in Minneapolis.  
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, Prince has been conducting a search for the "most beautiful girl in 
the world" to be his Valentine's Day "date" in a promotion for the song. The 
finalists will be announced soon. 
</P>
<P>
 And the retirement? 
</P>
<P>
 "He retired from recording as Prince," she says of the artist, who has adopted 
that male-female symbol as his moniker. "This single will be released under his 
new name, for which we still don't have a spelling or pronunciation." STEVE 
HOCHMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
