<HEADLINE>
<P>
IT'S BIGOTRY TO LUMP WHITE STUDENTS TOGETHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Your story "Plan for Black Students' Conference Draws Fire" (Jan. 13) uses 
the term Anglos in referring to 19% of Reseda High School's students. 
</P>
<P>
 It is bigotry to lump all white students together as Anglos when there are 
many distinctive cultures represented in this group. 
</P>
<P>
 Although the school has a Brothers and Sisters United Club and a Latino Club, 
I doubt that it has an Anglo Club. I hope the instructional program of the 
school includes an appreciation of the cultures and concerns of white ethnics 
as well. 
</P>
<P>
 IRENE SZEWIOLA 
</P>
<P>
 North Hills 
