<P>
 More alternative rock albums are making the Top 10 these days. The latest to 
swoop in is Counting Crows' "August and Everything After," which debuted at No. 
6 on The Times' Southern California chart -- a notch ahead of Smashing 
Pumpkins' "Siamese Dream." Ace of Base just missed having two singles in the 
pop Top 10. Its new "Sign" is No. 8, while long-running "All That She Wants" is 
No. 11. Speaking of long-running hits, if you can believe it, Tag Team's 
"Whoomp! There It Is" -- a hot single last summer -- is still selling: No. 16 
on the local chart and No. 4 nationally. TOP 10 ALBUMS 03,04,41,11 Title, 
