<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOLTZ WINS NEWPORT CLASSIC IN PLAYOFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jerry Foltz, a Nike Tour pro from Phoenix, birdied the first hole of a 
three-way playoff to win the 20th Taco Bell Newport Classic pro-am golf 
tournament Saturday at the Newport Beach Country Club. 
</P>
<P>
 Foltz's three on the 339-yard par-four first hole was one better than Paul 
Stankowski of El Paso, Tex., and Sonny Skinner of Sylvester, Ga., and gave 
Foltz the $13,000 first prize from the purse of $70,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The three finished two rounds tied at six-under-par 136. Foltz shot a 
four-under 67 and Skinner a 69 to catch Stankowski, the first leader who 
ballooned to a 72 after an opening 64. 
</P>
<P>
 Three teams tied for the pro-am championship at 14-under 128: Foltz and Jim 
Glidewell of Newport Beach; Jeff Coston of Orlando, Fla., and Buz Knyal of Los 
Angeles, and Stankowski and John Jester of Mercer Island, Wash. 
</P>
</TEXT>
