<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: VENTURA; ARSON SUSPECTED IN VEGETATION FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A tough-to-reach vegetation fire burned about 20 acres in the Santa Clara 
riverbed late Saturday, creating an orange glow in the sky between Ventura and 
Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire -- which started in several spots and then burned together -- was 
reported to the Oxnard Fire Department at 7:30 p.m. and was about 90% contained 
shortly after 9 p.m., authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura city firefighters carried hoses through several hundred yards of thick 
bamboo to reach the front line of flames. Water was pumped from three tankers. 
Eight engines, one helicopter and one bulldozer also were assigned to the fire. 
</P>
<P>
 The nearest structure to the flames was radio station KBBY-FM on Olivas Park 
Drive, which firefighters used as a base for equipment. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials believe the fire was arson. 
</P>
<P>
 "We think it's probably mischievous," said Ventura Battalion Chief Brian 
Gordon. "We had three separate spots that were quite a ways away from each 
other." JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
