<P>
 A tip from county firefighters in Thousand Oaks led to the arrest of an 
18-year-old man on suspicion of vandalizing a city sign, authorities said 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Anthony Brewer was cited for misdemeanor vandalism Friday night and 
released, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 A week earlier, an engine company of firefighters saw someone running from a 
freshly spray-painted city sign near Lynn Road and Hillcrest Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 A nearby sheriff's deputy saw a car leaving, and interviewed the driver and 
passengers, but made no arrests. 
</P>
