<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 3; Column 3; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
133 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE IDENTIFY MAN SHOT IN SAN CLEMENTE DISPUTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Authorities have identified the victim of a shooting during a neighborhood 
dispute Friday as William Wallace Jolley, 32. 
</P>
<P>
 Jolley, who was shot through the abdomen, was in serious condition following 
surgery at Mission Hospital Regional Medical Center. His 10-year-old son, whose 
finger was wounded in the shooting, spent the night at Samaritan Medical 
Center-San Clemente, Orange County sheriff's officials said.  
</P>
<P>
 Deputies arrested Jolley's next door neighbor, Arthur Harry Triebel, 39, on 
suspicion of attempted murder. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told deputies that the incident began with an argument involving 
four members of Jolley's family in the driveway of Triebel's home in the 200 
block of West Escalones. Triebel attempted to intervene and began shooting a 
semiautomatic pistol, authorities said. 
</P>
