<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN FATALLY SHOT NEAR TIRE SHOP IN SANTA ANA; POLICE SEEK 3 MEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Orange man was shot to death in a pickup truck Friday night after an 
apparent confrontation with gang members outside a local tire shop, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim was identified as Zenen Bautista Delapaz, 29. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said that the victim, his brother and a friend were returning to the 
tire shop at 2701 S. Orange Ave. in Santa Ana just before 9 p.m. Friday when 
they were approached by three young men who asked them about buying tires. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim apparently worked at the site, police said. A shop called Delapaz 
Tires is listed at the address, but no one could be reached there Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 After an initial inquiry about tires, one of the would-be customers pulled out 
a dark-colored handgun and started shooting, firing six or seven rounds, Sgt. 
Anthony Levatino said.  
</P>
<P>
 Delapaz, who was driving the truck, was hit once and attempted to flee the 
scene. But he slumped over the wheel as the truck came to a stop about a block 
or so away, Levatino said.  
</P>
<P>
 He was dead by the time police arrived on the scene, but neither his brother 
nor his friend appeared to have been injured in the attack, the officer added. 
</P>
<P>
 The assailants fled the scene in an unidentified vehicle and were still at 
large Saturday night. Police believe they are gang members. 
</P>
