<P>
DRIVER RUNS OVER MAN, 52, LYING ON ROAD IN ANAHEIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 52-year-old man was run over by a car early Saturday while lying in a major 
roadway, but police aren't certain whether he was already dead at the time. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said they are unsure what the man was doing in the street or 
whether he may even have been struck by another vehicle before his body was 
discovered.An investigation is continuing, Anaheim Police Officer Dale Dambrun 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim lived in Fullerton, but his name was not released pending 
notification of his family. 
</P>
<P>
 Matthew Emard, 17, who was driving a 1981 Chevrolet Malibu, called police just 
after midnight to report that he had struck someone on westbound Orangethorpe 
Avenue, west of Raymond Avenue, near the railroad tracks, police said.  
</P>
<P>
 Emard of Anaheim was not arrested, and Dambrun said he did not appear to have 
been at fault. 
</P>
<P>
 Anaheim police are asking anyone with information about the incident to call 
(714) 254-1532. 
</P>
