<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: WILSHIRE CENTER; DEPUTY POLICE CHIEF TO ADDRESS FORUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Deputy Chief Lawrence E. Fetters, commanding officer of the Police 
Department's Human Resources Center, will speak at a Feb. 13 forum sponsored by 
Immanuel Presbyterian Church, 3300 Wilshire Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 The 1 p.m. forum will be preceded by worship service at 11 a.m. and a luncheon 
at 12:15 p.m. The lunch is $4 for adults and $2 for children younger than 12. 
</P>
<P>
 Fetters, who is also a member of the church's Heart of Los Angeles 
neighborhood youth ministry, will speak on police-community relations, 
particularly in the Wilshire Center area. Information: (213) 389-3191. 
</P>
</TEXT>
