<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIABETES SEMINAR OFFERED SATURDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The American Diabetes Assn.'s Latino programs committee will host a free 
Spanish-English education seminar Saturday at the AltaMed Senior Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The 8:30 a.m. to 3 p.m. seminar, "Yes, You Can . . . With Diabetes," will 
cover how to manage the disease with steps to take at home and at the doctor's 
office, exercise and nutrition. 
</P>
<P>
 The program's goal is to teach patients how to make healthy choices and 
lifestyle modifications to avoid blindness, stroke, heart attack, amputation 
and other complications associated with this chronic disease that impairs the 
body's ability to convert sugar into energy. 
</P>
<P>
 The AltaMed Senior Center is at 5425 E. Pomona Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration is required: (213) 381-3639 from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
