<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: WILSHIRE AREA; POLICE COMMANDER TO BE HONORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cmdr. Julius I. Davis, the former commanding officer at the Police 
Department's Wilshire Division who was recently promoted to commander of the 
Internal Affairs Group, will be honored by the community at a Feb. 18 dinner. 
</P>
<P>
 The Wilshire Area Community Coalition will honor Davis for his more than 25 
years of service, including more than three years at the helm of the Wilshire 
Division, said coalition president Marie Gaines. 
</P>
<P>
 "We want to recognize him for his personal dedication and service to our 
community," Gaines said.  
</P>
<P>
 The program will begin at 7 p.m. at the Sheraton Grande Hotel, S. 333 Figueroa 
St. Businesses, groups and individuals who want to participate are encouraged 
to make reservations by Saturday. 
</P>
